From a17d41de9ccec0a290081ae6adc2de6e117dc246 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: regksem <regksem@tuta.io>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 21:52:30 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add opt-in anti-bot subsystem (patch 0077)

New net.regksem.xwaterfall.antibot.AntiBot, wired into the login path:
- login-rate attack detector that flips the proxy into 'under attack' mode;
- reconnect 'firewall' (under attack): a new IP is kicked once and only let in
  after it reconnects within a configurable window;
- per-IP concurrent connection cap, accounted via BungeeCord add/removeConnection;
- username regex allow-list and, under attack, blocking of raw-IP joins.

All opt-in via antibot.* in xwaterfall.yml and disabled by default, so a stock
config is unchanged. The two attack-gated checks never touch normal players.

